32#if TF_USE_CUSTOM_EIGEN_PACK
33// WARNING: Most of the code here implicitly assumes that the matrix is in
34// ColMajor layout. This is guaranteed by the tensor contraction (see
35// TensorContraction.h).
36//
37// Inside Eigen a tensor contraction is represented by a matrix multiplication.
38// We don't want to actually extract image patches and reshape the result into
39// a matrix (this involves allocating huge extra memory), so the patch
40// extraction and reshape operations are implicit.
41//
42// TensorContractionInputMapper takes a matrix index and returns the coefficient
43// (or the packet) of the "virtual tensor", that would be at that index if we
44// were to actually reshape the result of patch extraction.
45//
46// TensorContractionSubMapper provides a similar view into the "virtual matrix"
47// at the given vertical and horizontal offsets.
48//
49// "Virtual matrix" dimensions:
50// *0: kernelChannels * kernelRows * kernelCols;
51// 1: out_height * out_width; * OTHERS (e.g batches, etc...)
52//
53// *) extracted patches are continuous in memory (innermost dimension assuming
54// col major layout)
55//
56// With this dimensions:
57// row - offset within a single patch (in code: patchId)
58// col - index of the extracted patch (in code: patchIndex)
59// patchIndex âˆˆ [0..num_patches * OTHERS] (batch and other dimensions)
60//
61// TODO(ezhulenev): Consolidate this part of the code with the image patch
62// extraction code since they are both very similar.
63
64template <typename NewDimension, Index Rows, Index Cols, typename ArgType,
65 typename Device, typename Scalar_, typename Index,
66 typename nocontract_t, typename contract_t, int Side, int packet_size,
67 bool inner_dim_contiguous, bool inner_dim_reordered, int Alignment>
68class TensorContractionInputMapper<
69 Scalar_, Index, Side,
70 TensorEvaluator<
71 const TensorReshapingOp<NewDimension,
72 const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
73 Device>,
74 nocontract_t, contract_t, packet_size, inner_dim_contiguous,
75 inner_dim_reordered, Alignment> {
76 public:
77 typedef Scalar_ Scalar;
78
79 typedef TensorContractionInputMapper<
80 Scalar, Index, Side,
81 TensorEvaluator<
82 const TensorReshapingOp<
83 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
84 Device>,
85 nocontract_t, contract_t, packet_size, inner_dim_contiguous,
86 inner_dim_reordered, Alignment>
87 Self;
88
89 typedef TensorContractionSubMapper<
90 Scalar, Index, Side,
91 TensorEvaluator<
92 const TensorReshapingOp<
93 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
94 Device>,
95 nocontract_t, contract_t, packet_size, inner_dim_contiguous,
96 inner_dim_reordered, Alignment>
97 SubMapper;
98
99 typedef SubMapper VectorMapper;
100 typedef SubMapper LinearMapper;
101 typedef typename packet_traits<Scalar>::type Packet;
102
103 typedef TensorEvaluator<ArgType, Device> TensorEvaluatorT;
104
105 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
106 TensorContractionInputMapper(
107 const TensorEvaluator<
108 const TensorReshapingOp<
109 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
110 Device>& tensor,
111 const nocontract_t&, const nocontract_t&, const contract_t&,
112 const contract_t&)
113 : m_impl(tensor.impl().impl()) {
114 Index patch_rows;
115 Index patch_depth;
116 if (internal::traits<ArgType>::Layout == ColMajor) {
117 patch_depth = tensor.impl().dimensions()[0];
118 patch_rows = tensor.impl().dimensions()[1];
119 m_patch_cols = tensor.impl().dimensions()[2];
120 m_num_patches = tensor.impl().dimensions()[3];
121 } else {
122 const size_t NumDims = tensor.impl().dimensions().size();
123 patch_depth = tensor.impl().dimensions()[NumDims - 1];
124 patch_rows = tensor.impl().dimensions()[NumDims - 2];
125 m_patch_cols = tensor.impl().dimensions()[NumDims - 3];
126 m_num_patches = tensor.impl().dimensions()[NumDims - 4];
127 }
128
129 // Strides for navigating through the single patch.
130 m_patch_row_stride = patch_depth;
131 m_patch_col_stride = patch_rows * m_patch_row_stride;
132
133 m_patch_row_inflate_strides = tensor.impl().rowInflateStride();
134 m_patch_col_inflate_strides = tensor.impl().colInflateStride();
135
136 m_colStride = patch_rows;
137
138 m_outputRows = tensor.impl().outputRows();
139 m_outputCols = tensor.impl().outputCols();
140 m_row_strides = tensor.impl().userRowStride();
141 m_col_strides = tensor.impl().userColStride();
142
143 m_in_row_strides = tensor.impl().userInRowStride();
144 m_in_col_strides = tensor.impl().userInColStride();
145
146 if (internal::traits<ArgType>::Layout == ColMajor) {
147 m_inputRows = tensor.impl().impl().dimensions()[1];
148 m_inputCols = tensor.impl().impl().dimensions()[2];
149 } else {
150 const int NumDims = tensor.impl().impl().dimensions().size();
151 m_inputRows = tensor.impl().impl().dimensions()[NumDims - 2];
152 m_inputCols = tensor.impl().impl().dimensions()[NumDims - 3];
153 }
154
155 m_rowInputStride = patch_depth;
156 m_colInputStride = patch_depth * m_inputRows;
157 m_patchInputStride = patch_depth * m_inputRows * m_inputCols;
158
159 m_rowPaddingTop = tensor.impl().rowPaddingTop();
160 m_colPaddingLeft = tensor.impl().colPaddingLeft();
161
162 m_fastPatchRowStride =
163 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index>(m_patch_row_stride);
164 m_fastPatchColStride =
165 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index>(m_patch_col_stride);
166 m_fastInputRowStride =
167 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index>(m_patch_row_inflate_strides);
168 m_fastInputColStride =
169 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index>(m_patch_col_inflate_strides);
170 m_fastNumPatches = internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index>(m_num_patches);
171 m_fastColStride = internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index>(m_colStride);
172 m_fastOutputRows = internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index>(m_outputRows);
173 m_fastDimZero = internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index>(patch_depth);
174 }
175
176 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
177 TensorContractionInputMapper(const TensorContractionInputMapper& base_mapper)
178 : m_impl(base_mapper.m_impl) {
179 m_patch_cols = base_mapper.m_patch_cols;
180 m_num_patches = base_mapper.m_num_patches;
181
182 m_patch_row_stride = base_mapper.m_patch_row_stride;
183 m_patch_col_stride = base_mapper.m_patch_col_stride;
184
185 m_patch_row_inflate_strides = base_mapper.m_patch_row_inflate_strides;
186 m_patch_col_inflate_strides = base_mapper.m_patch_col_inflate_strides;
187
188 m_colStride = base_mapper.m_colStride;
189
190 m_rowInputStride = base_mapper.m_rowInputStride;
191 m_colInputStride = base_mapper.m_colInputStride;
192 m_patchInputStride = base_mapper.m_patchInputStride;
193
194 m_inputRows = base_mapper.m_inputRows;
195 m_inputCols = base_mapper.m_inputCols;
196
197 m_outputRows = base_mapper.m_outputRows;
198 m_outputCols = base_mapper.m_outputCols;
199 m_row_strides = base_mapper.m_row_strides;
200 m_col_strides = base_mapper.m_col_strides;
201
202 m_in_row_strides = base_mapper.m_in_row_strides;
203 m_in_col_strides = base_mapper.m_in_col_strides;
204
205 m_rowPaddingTop = base_mapper.m_rowPaddingTop;
206 m_colPaddingLeft = base_mapper.m_colPaddingLeft;
207
208 m_fastPatchRowStride = base_mapper.m_fastPatchRowStride;
209 m_fastPatchColStride = base_mapper.m_fastPatchColStride;
210 m_fastInputRowStride = base_mapper.m_fastInputRowStride;
211 m_fastInputColStride = base_mapper.m_fastInputColStride;
212 m_fastNumPatches = base_mapper.m_fastNumPatches;
213 m_fastColStride = base_mapper.m_fastColStride;
214 m_fastOutputRows = base_mapper.m_fastOutputRows;
215 m_fastDimZero = base_mapper.m_fastDimZero;
216 }

218 // If true, turns off some optimizations for loading packets since the image
219 // patches are "non-standard" such as there are non-trivial strides or
220 // inflations in the input.
221 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
222 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE bool nonStandardPatches() const {
223 return m_in_row_strides != 1 || m_in_col_strides != 1 ||
224 m_patch_row_inflate_strides != 1 || m_patch_col_inflate_strides != 1;
225 }

229 return SubMapper(*this, i, j);
230 }

232 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
233 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE LinearMapper getLinearMapper(Index i, Index j) const {
234 return LinearMapper(*this, i, j);

239 Index rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex;
240 computeBaseIndices(0, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
241 return loadCoeff(row, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
242 }

244 // Load the coefficient at the patchIndex location instead of the usual
245 // m_rowIndex,
246 // m_colIndex, m_otherIndex. This is currently only used by the gpu code.
247 // EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC

250 Index rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex;
251 computeBaseIndices(patchIndex, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
252 return loadCoeff(row, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);

257 Index rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex;
258 computeBaseIndices(0, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
259 return loadPacket(row, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);

273 return m_impl;

283 private:
284 friend class TensorContractionSubMapper<
285 Scalar, Index, Side,
286 TensorEvaluator<
287 const TensorReshapingOp<

292
293 // Load coefficient from a patch specified by the "within patch offset"
294 // (patchId) and the precomputed indices of the first element of the patch.
295 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
296 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE Scalar loadCoeff(Index patchId, Index rowIndex,
297 Index colIndex, Index otherIndex) const {
298 // Find the offset of the element wrt the location of the first element.
299 const Index patchOffset = patchId / m_fastDimZero;
300
301 const Index colOffset = patchOffset / m_fastColStride;
302 const Index inputCol = colIndex + colOffset * m_in_col_strides;
303 const Index origInputCol =
304 (m_patch_col_inflate_strides == 1)
305 ? inputCol
306 : ((inputCol >= 0) ? (inputCol / m_fastInputColStride) : 0);
307
308 const Index rowOffset = patchOffset - colOffset * m_colStride;
309 const Index inputRow = rowIndex + rowOffset * m_in_row_strides;
310 const Index origInputRow =
311 (m_patch_row_inflate_strides == 1)
312 ? inputRow
313 : ((inputRow >= 0) ? (inputRow / m_fastInputRowStride) : 0);
314 if (origInputCol < 0 || origInputRow < 0 || origInputCol >= m_inputCols ||
315 origInputRow >= m_inputRows ||
316 (inputCol != origInputCol * m_patch_col_inflate_strides) ||
317 (inputRow != origInputRow * m_patch_row_inflate_strides)) {
318 return Scalar(0);
319 }
320 const Index depth = patchId - patchOffset * patchDepth();
321 const Index inputIndex = depth + origInputRow * m_rowInputStride +
322 origInputCol * m_colInputStride + otherIndex;
323 return m_impl.coeff(inputIndex);
324 }
325
326 // This is the same as loadCoeff(...), but optimized for all `inflate_strides`
327 // and `in_strides` equal to 1 (template specialization without templates).
328 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
329 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE Scalar loadCoeffStandard(Index patchId, Index rowIndex,
330 Index colIndex,
331 Index otherIndex) const {
332 eigen_assert(!nonStandardPatches());
333
334 // Find the offset of the element wrt the location of the first element.
335 const Index patchOffset = patchId / m_fastDimZero;
336 const Index colOffset = patchOffset / m_fastColStride;
337 const Index rowOffset = patchOffset - colOffset * m_colStride;
338 const Index inputCol = colIndex + colOffset;
339 const Index inputRow = rowIndex + rowOffset;
340 if (inputCol < 0 || inputCol >= m_inputCols || inputRow < 0 ||
341 inputRow >= m_inputRows) {
342 return Scalar(0);
343 }
344 const Index depth = patchId - patchOffset * patchDepth();
345 const Index inputIndex = depth + inputRow * m_rowInputStride +
346 inputCol * m_colInputStride + otherIndex;
347 return m_impl.coeff(inputIndex);
348 }
349
350 // Load packet from a patch specified by the "within patch offset"
351 // (patchId) and the precomputed indices of the first element of the patch.
352 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
353 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Packet loadPacket(Index patchId, Index rowIndex,
354 Index colIndex,
355 Index otherIndex) const {
356 const Index packetSize = internal::unpacket_traits<Packet>::size;
357 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT(packetSize > 1, YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE)
358 eigen_assert(patchId < patchDepth() * patchRows() * m_patch_cols);
359
360 if (nonStandardPatches()) {
361 return packetWithPossibleZero(patchId, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
362 }
363 typedef decltype(m_impl) TensorEvaluatorT;
364 return loadPacketStandard<Packet, TensorEvaluatorT>(patchId, rowIndex,
365 colIndex, otherIndex);
366 }
367
368 // Helper function to load a 'partial' packet - this is the single column
369 // part of a packet that is split across two columns. In the 'partial' packet,
370 // the elements corresponding to the column (specified through colOffset) are
371 // loaded and the rest of the elements are zero-filled into the 'partial'
372 // packet. This function is called from loadPacketStandardFromTwoColumns().
373 // This code path is exercised only when the packet type supports masked load
374 // and when the partial packet load is available in the TensorEvaluator.
375 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
376 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Packet loadPartialPacketStandard(
377 Index rowIndex, Index colIndex, Index otherIndex, Index patchId,
378 const Index span[], const Index patchOffsets[], Index colOffset) const {
379 const Index inputCol = colIndex + colOffset;
380 const Index rowOffsets[2] = {patchOffsets[0] - colOffset * m_colStride,
381 patchOffsets[1] - colOffset * m_colStride};
382 const Index inputRows[2] = {rowIndex + rowOffsets[0],
383 rowIndex + rowOffsets[1]};
384
385 if (inputRows[0] >= m_inputRows || inputRows[1] < 0 ||
386 inputCol >= m_inputCols || inputCol < 0) {
387 // Partial packet is all zeros
388 return internal::pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0));
389 } else if (inputRows[0] >= 0 && inputRows[1] < m_inputRows) {
390 // From inputIndex-span[0], we need to load elements starting from index
391 // span[0] all the way upto (and including) span[1].
392 const Index depth = patchId - patchOffsets[0] * patchDepth();
393 const Index inputIndex = depth + inputRows[0] * m_rowInputStride +
394 inputCol * m_colInputStride + otherIndex;
395 return m_impl.template partialPacket<Packet>(
396 inputIndex - span[0], mask<Packet>(span[0], span[1] + 1));
397 } else {
398 // Using slow path for this partial packet.
399 // We need to load elements starting from index span[0] all the way upto
400 // (and including) span[1]. We split this load into 3 parts:
401 // 0 : span[0]-1 - Zeros will be loaded for these indices
402 // span[0] : span[1] - Elements will be loaded here for these indices
403 // span[1]+1 : packetSize-1 - Zeross will be loaded for these indices
404 const Index packetSize = internal::unpacket_traits<Packet>::size;
405 EIGEN_ALIGN_MAX
406 typename internal::remove_const<Scalar>::type values[packetSize];
407 for (int i = 0; i < span[0]; ++i) values[i] = Scalar(0);
408 for (int i = span[0]; i < span[1] + 1; ++i)
409 values[i] =
410 loadCoeff(patchId - span[0] + i, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
411 for (int i = span[1] + 1; i < packetSize; ++i) values[i] = Scalar(0);
412 return internal::pload<Packet>(values);
413 }
414 }
415
416 // Helper function to load a packet that is split across two columns.
417 // If required, this function is called from loadPacketStandard() when the
418 // packet type supports masked load and when the partial packet load is
419 // available in the TensorEvaluator.
420 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
421 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Packet loadPacketStandardFromTwoColumns(
422 Index patchId, Index rowIndex, Index colIndex, Index otherIndex,
423 const Index patchOffsets[], const Index colOffsets[]) const {
424 eigen_assert(colOffsets[1] == colOffsets[0] + 1);
425 const Index packetSize = internal::unpacket_traits<Packet>::size;
426
427 // Packet to load will be split into 2 parts where each part spans a single
428 // column. First determine where to split.
429 const Index patchIdSplit =
430 ((colOffsets[1] * m_colStride) * m_rowInputStride) - 1;
431 const Index patchOffsetSplit = patchIdSplit / m_fastDimZero;
432
433 // patchIds[i]: patchId corresponding to partial packet i
434 // spans[i]: Start and end indices corresponding to the elements
435 // to be loaded for partial packet i
436 // patchOffsets2Cols[i]: patchOffsets corresponding to partial packet i
437 const Index patchIds[2] = {patchId, patchIdSplit + 1};
438 const Index spans[2][2] = {{0, patchIdSplit - patchId},
439 {patchIdSplit - patchId + 1, packetSize - 1}};
440 const Index patchOffsets2Cols[2][2] = {
441 {patchOffsets[0], patchOffsetSplit},
442 {patchOffsetSplit + 1, patchOffsets[1]}};
443
444 // Load partial packets and do bit-wise OR to generate required packet
445 return internal::por<Packet>(
446 loadPartialPacketStandard(rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex, patchIds[0],
447 spans[0], patchOffsets2Cols[0],
448 colOffsets[0]),
449 loadPartialPacketStandard(rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex, patchIds[1],
450 spans[1], patchOffsets2Cols[1],
451 colOffsets[1]));
452 }
453
454 // Helper function to load a packet that is present in a single columns.
455 // If required, this function is called from loadPacketStandard().
456 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
457 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Packet loadPacketStandardFromSingleColumn(
458 Index patchId, Index rowIndex, Index colIndex, Index otherIndex,
459 const Index patchOffsets[], const Index colOffsets[],
460 const Index inputCols[]) const {
461 eigen_assert(colOffsets[0] == colOffsets[1]);
462 const Index rowOffsets[2] = {patchOffsets[0] - colOffsets[0] * m_colStride,
463 patchOffsets[1] - colOffsets[1] * m_colStride};
464 eigen_assert(rowOffsets[0] <= rowOffsets[1]);
465 const Index inputRows[2] = {rowIndex + rowOffsets[0],
466 rowIndex + rowOffsets[1]};
467
468 if (inputRows[0] >= m_inputRows || inputRows[1] < 0) {
469 // all zeros
470 return internal::pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0)); // all zeros
471 }
472
473 if (inputRows[0] >= 0 && inputRows[1] < m_inputRows) {
474 // no padding
475 const Index depth = patchId - patchOffsets[0] * patchDepth();
476 const Index inputIndex = depth + inputRows[0] * m_rowInputStride +
477 inputCols[0] * m_colInputStride + otherIndex;
478 return m_impl.template packet<Unaligned>(inputIndex);
479 }
480 return packetWithPossibleZero(patchId, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
481 }
482
483 // Load standard packet from a patch specified by the "within patch offset"
484 // (patchId) and the precomputed indices of the first element of the patch.
485 // This function will be called if partial packet loading is not available
486 // for the TensorEvaluator or if the packet type does not support masked
487 // load.
488 template <typename PacketT, typename TensorEvaluatorT>
489 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE typename std::enable_if<
490 !TensorEvaluatorHasPartialPacket<TensorEvaluatorT, PacketT, Index>::value,
491 PacketT>::type
492 loadPacketStandard(Index patchId, Index rowIndex, Index colIndex,
493 Index otherIndex) const {
494 const Index packetSize = internal::unpacket_traits<Packet>::size;
495 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT(packetSize > 1, YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE)
496 eigen_assert(patchId < patchDepth() * patchRows() * m_patch_cols);
497
498 eigen_assert(!nonStandardPatches());
499
500 if ((patchDepth() % packetSize) == 0) {
501 return loadPacketFast(patchId, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
502 }
503
504 // Offsets and input calculation here are identical to
505 // loadCoeffStandard(...), but repeated twice.
506 const Index patchOffsets[2] = {patchId / m_fastDimZero,
507 (patchId + packetSize - 1) / m_fastDimZero};
508 const Index colOffsets[2] = {patchOffsets[0] / m_fastColStride,
509 patchOffsets[1] / m_fastColStride};
510 const Index inputCols[2] = {colIndex + colOffsets[0],
511 colIndex + colOffsets[1]};
512
513 if (inputCols[0] >= m_inputCols || inputCols[1] < 0) {
514 // all zeros
515 return internal::pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0));
516 }
517 if (inputCols[0] == inputCols[1]) {
518 return loadPacketStandardFromSingleColumn(patchId, rowIndex, colIndex,
519 otherIndex, patchOffsets,
520 colOffsets, inputCols);
521 }
522 return packetWithPossibleZero(patchId, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
523 }
524
525 // Load standard packet from a patch specified by the "within patch offset"
526 // (patchId) and the precomputed indices of the first element of the patch.
527 // This function will be called if partial packet loading is available for
528 // the TensorEvaluator and if the packet type supports masked load.
529 // The only difference between this and the other case is that if the packet
530 // to load is split across two columns, then in this case instead of going to
531 // the slow (element-by-element) load, we load two packets - each containing
532 // elements from one of the columns (rest of the elements of the packets are
533 // zeroes), and then combine these two packets to generate the required
534 // packet. The idea is to enable fast load (if possible) of these 'partial'
535 // packets.
536 template <typename PacketT, typename TensorEvaluatorT>
537 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE typename std::enable_if<
538 TensorEvaluatorHasPartialPacket<TensorEvaluatorT, PacketT, Index>::value,
539 PacketT>::type
540 loadPacketStandard(Index patchId, Index rowIndex, Index colIndex,
541 Index otherIndex) const {
542 const Index packetSize = internal::unpacket_traits<PacketT>::size;
543 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT(packetSize > 1, YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE)
544 eigen_assert(patchId < patchDepth() * patchRows() * m_patch_cols);
545
546 eigen_assert(!nonStandardPatches());
547
548 if ((patchDepth() % packetSize) == 0) {
549 return loadPacketFast(patchId, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
550 }
551
552 // Offsets and input calculation here are identical to
553 // loadCoeffStandard(...), but repeated twice.
554 const Index patchOffsets[2] = {patchId / m_fastDimZero,
555 (patchId + packetSize - 1) / m_fastDimZero};
556 const Index colOffsets[2] = {patchOffsets[0] / m_fastColStride,
557 patchOffsets[1] / m_fastColStride};
558 const Index inputCols[2] = {colIndex + colOffsets[0],
559 colIndex + colOffsets[1]};
560
561 if (inputCols[0] >= m_inputCols || inputCols[1] < 0) {
562 // all zeros
563 return internal::pset1<PacketT>(Scalar(0));
564 }
565 if (inputCols[0] == inputCols[1]) {
566 return loadPacketStandardFromSingleColumn(patchId, rowIndex, colIndex,
567 otherIndex, patchOffsets,
568 colOffsets, inputCols);
569 }
570 if (inputCols[1] == inputCols[0] + 1) {
571 return loadPacketStandardFromTwoColumns(
572 patchId, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex, patchOffsets, colOffsets);
573 }
574 return packetWithPossibleZero(patchId, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
575 }
576
577 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
578 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Packet loadPacketFast(Index patchId, Index rowIndex,
579 Index colIndex,
580 Index otherIndex) const {
581 const Index packetSize = internal::unpacket_traits<Packet>::size;
582 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT(packetSize > 1, YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE)
583 eigen_assert(patchId < patchDepth() * patchRows() * m_patch_cols);
584
585 eigen_assert(!nonStandardPatches());
586 eigen_assert((patchDepth() % packetSize) == 0);
587 // Find the offset of the element wrt the location of the first element.
588 const Index patchOffset = patchId / m_fastDimZero;
589 eigen_assert((patchId + packetSize - 1) / m_fastDimZero == patchOffset);
590
591 const Index colOffset = patchOffset / m_fastColStride;
592 const Index rowOffset = patchOffset - colOffset * m_colStride;
593 const Index inputCol = colIndex + colOffset;
594 const Index inputRow = rowIndex + rowOffset;
595 if (inputCol < 0 || inputRow < 0 || inputCol >= m_inputCols ||
596 inputRow >= m_inputRows) {
597 // all zeros
598 return internal::pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0));
599 }
600 // no padding
601 const Index depth = patchId - patchOffset * patchDepth();
602 const Index inputIndex = depth + inputRow * m_rowInputStride +
603 inputCol * m_colInputStride + otherIndex;
604 return m_impl.template packet<Unaligned>(inputIndex);
605 }
606
607 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Packet packetWithPossibleZero(
608 Index patchId, Index rowIndex, Index colIndex, Index otherIndex) const {
609 const int packetSize = internal::unpacket_traits<Packet>::size;
610 EIGEN_ALIGN_MAX
611 typename internal::remove_const<Scalar>::type values[packetSize];
612 for (int i = 0; i < packetSize; ++i) {
613 values[i] = loadCoeff(patchId + i, rowIndex, colIndex, otherIndex);
614 }
615 Packet rslt = internal::pload<Packet>(values);
616 return rslt;
617 }
618
619 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void computeBaseIndices(
620 Index patchIndex, Index& rowIndex, Index& colIndex,
621 Index& otherIndex) const {
622 const size_t NumInputDims = array_size<
623 typename TensorEvaluator<ArgType, Device>::Dimensions>::value;
624 otherIndex = (NumInputDims == 3) ? 0 : patchIndex / m_fastNumPatches;
625 const Index patch2DIndex = (NumInputDims == 3)
626 ? patchIndex
627 : (patchIndex - otherIndex * m_num_patches);
628 otherIndex *= m_patchInputStride;
629 colIndex = patch2DIndex / m_fastOutputRows;
630 rowIndex = patch2DIndex - colIndex * m_outputRows;
631 colIndex = colIndex * m_col_strides - m_colPaddingLeft;
632 rowIndex = rowIndex * m_row_strides - m_rowPaddingTop;
633 }
634
635 Index m_patch_cols; // number of columns in the patch
636 Index m_num_patches; // number of patches to extract.
637
638 // Strides for navigating through the single patch.
639 Index m_patch_row_stride;
640 Index m_patch_col_stride;
641 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index> m_fastPatchRowStride;
642 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index> m_fastPatchColStride;
643
644 Index m_patch_row_inflate_strides; // the strides for row inflation in the
645 // image patch
646 Index m_patch_col_inflate_strides; // the strides for col inflation in the
647 // image patch
648 // Fast representation of inflation strides.
649 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index> m_fastInputRowStride;
650 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index> m_fastInputColStride;
651
652 Index m_otherStride;
653 Index m_colStride;
654 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index> m_fastNumPatches;
655 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index> m_fastColStride;
656
657 Index m_rowInputStride; // row stride in the input tensor
658 Index m_colInputStride; // col stride in the input tensor
659 Index m_patchInputStride; // patch stride in the input tensor
660
661 Index m_inputRows; // Number of rows in the input tensor
662 Index m_inputCols; // Number of cols in the input tensor
663
664 Index m_outputRows; // Number of convolution output rows
665 Index m_outputCols; // Number of convolution output column
666
667 Index m_row_strides; // User specified row stride
668 Index m_col_strides; // User specified col stride
669
670 Index m_in_row_strides; // User specified input row stride
671 Index m_in_col_strides; // User specified input col stride
672
673 Index m_rowPaddingTop; // Row padding
674 Index m_colPaddingLeft; // Column padding
675
676 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index> m_fastOutputRows;
677 internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index> m_fastDimZero;
678
679 const TensorEvaluator<ArgType, Device> m_impl;
680};
681

689 const TensorReshapingOp<NewDimension,
690 const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
691 Device>,
692 nocontract_t, contract_t, packet_size, inner_dim_contiguous,
693 inner_dim_reordered, Alignment> {
694 public:
695 typedef typename packet_traits<Scalar>::type Packet;
696 typedef typename packet_traits<Scalar>::half HalfPacket;
697
698 typedef TensorContractionInputMapper<
699 Scalar, Index, Side,
700 TensorEvaluator<
701 const TensorReshapingOp<
702 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
703 Device>,
704 nocontract_t, contract_t, packet_size, inner_dim_contiguous,
705 inner_dim_reordered, Alignment>
706 ParentMapper;
707
708 typedef TensorContractionSubMapper<
709 Scalar, Index, Side,
710 TensorEvaluator<
711 const TensorReshapingOp<
712 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
713 Device>,
714 nocontract_t, contract_t, packet_size, inner_dim_contiguous,
715 inner_dim_reordered, Alignment>
716 Self;
717
718 typedef Self LinearMapper;
719
720 typedef typename ParentMapper::TensorEvaluatorT TensorEvaluatorT;

722 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE TensorContractionSubMapper(
723 const ParentMapper& base_mapper, Index vert_offset, Index horiz_offset)
724 : m_depth_offset(vert_offset),
725 m_col_offset(horiz_offset),
726 m_base_mapper(base_mapper) {

730 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE TensorContractionSubMapper(

740 m_otherIndex);
741 }

772 template <typename Packet>
773 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC bool aligned(Index) const {
774 return false;
775 }

777 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
778 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE bool nonStandardPatches() const {
779 return m_base_mapper.nonStandardPatches();
780 }
781
782 // Max(Col|Row|Depth): compute the upper limit for the column, row and depth
783 // index respectively that fits into the peeled_k elements starting at
784 // m_depth_offset.
785
786 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
787 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index maxCol(const Index peeled_k) const {
788 const Index max_col =
789 (m_depth_offset + (peeled_k == 0 ? 0 : peeled_k - 1)) /
790 fastPatchColStride();
791 return std::min<Index>(1 + max_col, patchCols());
792 }
793
794 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
795 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index maxRow(const Index peeled_k,
796 const Index col) const {
797 const Index max_row = (m_depth_offset + (peeled_k == 0 ? 0 : peeled_k - 1) -
798 col * patchColStride()) /
799 fastPatchRowStride();
800 return std::min<Index>(1 + max_row, patchRows());
801 }
802
803 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
804 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index maxDepth(const Index peeled_k, const Index col,
805 Index row) const {
806 const Index max_depth = m_depth_offset + peeled_k - //
807 col * patchColStride() - //
808 row * patchRowStride();
809 return std::min<Index>(max_depth, patchDepth());
810 }
811
812 // MaxDepth uses only the remaining number of elements in the peeled_k.
813 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
814 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index maxDepth(const Index num_elements,
815 const Index start_depth) const {
816 return std::min<Index>(start_depth + num_elements, patchDepth());
817 }
818
819 // Every register matters in this code, so sometimes to prevent register
820 // spilling, instead of the variable that you would expect to see, we use
821 // another one, that is guaranteed to have the same value. E.g. patch depth is
822 // always the same as input depth, and it's also the same as input row stride.
823 // Bunch of other parameters have similar relations.
824
825 typedef internal::TensorIntDivisor<Index> IndexDivisor;
826
827 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
828 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index patchDepth() const {
829 return m_base_mapper.m_rowInputStride;
830 }
831 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
832 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index patchRows() const {
833 return m_base_mapper.m_colStride;
834 }
835 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
836 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index patchCols() const {
837 return m_base_mapper.m_patch_cols;
838 }
839
840 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
841 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index patchRowStride() const {
842 eigen_assert(patchDepth() == m_base_mapper.m_patch_row_stride &&
843 "Patch depth must be equal to patch row stride.");
844 return patchDepth();
845 }
846 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
847 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index patchColStride() const {
848 return m_base_mapper.m_patch_col_stride;
849 }
850
851 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
852 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE IndexDivisor fastPatchRowStride() const {
853 eigen_assert(patchDepth() == m_base_mapper.m_patch_row_stride &&
854 "Patch depth must be equal to patch row stride.");
855 return m_base_mapper.m_fastDimZero; // patch_depth
856 }
857 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
858 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE IndexDivisor fastPatchColStride() const {
859 return m_base_mapper.m_fastPatchColStride;
860 }
861
862 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
863 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Packet packetNoPadding(const Index depth,
864 const Index baseIndex) const {
865 const Index inputIndex = depth + baseIndex;
866 return m_base_mapper.m_impl.template packet<Unaligned>(inputIndex);
867 }
868 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
869 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Scalar coeffNoPadding(const Index depth,
870 const Index baseIndex) const {
871 const Index inputIndex = depth + baseIndex;
872 return m_base_mapper.m_impl.coeff(inputIndex);
873 }
874 template <typename PacketT = Packet>
875 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE typename std::enable_if<
876 TensorEvaluatorHasPartialPacket<TensorEvaluatorT, PacketT, Index>::value,
877 PacketT>::type
878 partialPacketNoPadding(const Index depth, const Index baseIndex,
879 Index num_coeffs) const {
880 const Index inputIndex = depth + baseIndex;
881 return m_base_mapper.m_impl.template partialPacket<PacketT>(
882 inputIndex, mask<PacketT>(0, num_coeffs));
883 }
884 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
885 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE bool hasPadding() const {
886 // TODO(ezhulenev): It does seems that for inflated filter it's still
887 // possible to guarantee "no padding or skipping" for non-standard packing.
888 if (nonStandardPatches()) return true;
889
890 // Non zero padding before.
891 if (m_base_mapper.m_rowPaddingTop > 0) return true;
892 if (m_base_mapper.m_colPaddingLeft > 0) return true;
893
894 // Non zero padding after in rows.
895 const Index last_row =
896 (m_base_mapper.m_outputRows - 1) * m_base_mapper.m_row_strides;
897 if (last_row + (patchRows() - 1) >= m_base_mapper.m_inputRows) return true;
898
899 // Non zero padding after in cols.
900 const Index last_col =
901 (m_base_mapper.m_outputCols - 1) * m_base_mapper.m_col_strides;
902 if (last_col + (patchCols() - 1) >= m_base_mapper.m_inputCols) return true;
903
904 return false;
905 }
906 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
907 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE bool padRow(const Index row) const {
908 const Index r = m_rowIndex + row;
909 return r < 0 || r >= m_base_mapper.m_inputRows;
910 }
911 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
912 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE bool padAnyRow(const Index first_row,
913 const Index last_row) const {
914 return m_rowIndex + first_row < 0 ||
915 m_rowIndex + last_row >= m_base_mapper.m_inputRows;
916 }
917 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
918 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE bool padOrSkipRow(const Index row,
919 Index* orig_row) const {
920 eigen_assert(nonStandardPatches());
921
922 const Index input_row = m_rowIndex + row * m_base_mapper.m_in_row_strides;
923 *orig_row = (m_base_mapper.m_patch_row_inflate_strides == 1)
924 ? input_row
925 : ((input_row >= 0)
926 ? (input_row / m_base_mapper.m_fastInputRowStride)
927 : 0);
928
929 return (*orig_row < 0 || *orig_row >= m_base_mapper.m_inputRows) ||
930 (input_row != *orig_row * m_base_mapper.m_patch_row_inflate_strides);
931 }
932 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
933 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE bool padCol(const Index col) const {
934 const Index c = m_colIndex + col;
935 return c < 0 || c >= m_base_mapper.m_inputCols;
936 }
937 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
938 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE bool padOrSkipCol(const Index col,
939 Index* orig_col) const {
940 eigen_assert(nonStandardPatches());
941
942 const Index input_col = m_colIndex + col * m_base_mapper.m_in_col_strides;
943 *orig_col = (m_base_mapper.m_patch_col_inflate_strides == 1)
944 ? input_col
945 : ((input_col >= 0)
946 ? (input_col / m_base_mapper.m_fastInputColStride)
947 : 0);
948
949 return (*orig_col < 0 || *orig_col >= m_base_mapper.m_inputCols) ||
950 (input_col != *orig_col * m_base_mapper.m_patch_col_inflate_strides);
951 }
952 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
953 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index baseIndex(const Index row, const Index col) const {
954 const Index r = m_rowIndex + row;
955 const Index c = m_colIndex + col;
956 return r * m_base_mapper.m_rowInputStride +
957 c * m_base_mapper.m_colInputStride + m_otherIndex;
958 }
959 // Compute a base index when original input row and column were precomputed
960 // using padOrSkipRow and padOrSkipCol. Used only for non standard patches.
961 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
962 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index origBaseIndex(const Index orig_row,
963 const Index orig_col) const {
964 return orig_row * m_base_mapper.m_rowInputStride +
965 orig_col * m_base_mapper.m_colInputStride + m_otherIndex;
966 }
967
968 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
969 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index rowStride() const {
970 return m_base_mapper.m_row_strides;
971 }
972 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
973 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index colStride() const {
974 return m_base_mapper.m_col_strides;
975 }
976
977 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
978 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index rowOffset() const {
979 const Index patchOffset = m_depth_offset / m_base_mapper.m_fastDimZero;
980 const Index colOffset = patchOffset / m_base_mapper.m_fastColStride;
981 return patchOffset - colOffset * m_base_mapper.m_colStride;
982 }
983
984 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
985 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index colOffset() const {
986 const Index patchOffset = m_depth_offset / m_base_mapper.m_fastDimZero;
987 const Index colOffset = patchOffset / m_base_mapper.m_fastColStride;
988 return colOffset;
989 }
990
991 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
992 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index depthOffset() const {
993 return m_depth_offset % patchDepth();
994 }
995
996 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE LinearMapper
997 getLinearMapper(Index i, Index j) const {
998 return LinearMapper(m_base_mapper, i + m_depth_offset, j + m_col_offset);
999 }
1000
1001 private:
1002 Index m_depth_offset; // First row in the input matrix
1003 Index m_col_offset; // First col in the input matrix
1004
1005 // Knowing that: col_offset == patchIndex * OTHERS, we keep precomputed base
1006 // indices for the first element in a patch specified by col_offset
1007 // (see computeBaseIndices(...) for details).
1008 Index m_rowIndex;
1009 Index m_colIndex;
1010 Index m_otherIndex;
1011
1012 const ParentMapper m_base_mapper; // Keeping a copy instead of a reference
1013 // performs better in benchmarks.
1014};
1015
1016// Arrange a block of the right input matrix (in our case it's always a "virtual
1017// matrix" constructed from extracted image patches) in contiguous memory.
1018//
1019// Given column major input (A0 beside A1 in memory):
1020// A0 B0 C0 D0 E0 F0 G0 H0 ... Z0
1021// A1 B1 C1 D1 E1 F1 G1 H1 ... Z1
1022// A2 B2 C2 D2 E2 F2 G2 H2 ... Z2
1023// A3 B3 C3 D3 E3 F3 G3 H3 ... Z3
1024// A4 B4 C4 D4 E4 F4 G4 H4 ... Z4
1025// A5 B5 C5 D5 E5 F5 G5 H5 ... Z5
1026// A6 B6 C6 D6 E6 F6 G6 H6 ... Z6
1027// A7 B7 C7 D7 E7 F7 G7 H7 ... Z7
1028// A8 ...
1029// ...
1030//
1031// *) A, B, C, ... - patches extracted from the original input.
1032// *) A0, A1, A2 ... - values from the same patch at different offsets.
1033//
1034// The traversal (packed rhs memory) order (B0 besides A0 in memory):
1035// A0 B0 C0 D0 A1 B1 C1 D1 ...
1036// E0 F0 G0 H0 E1 F1 G1 H1 ...
1037// ...
1038// Z0 Z1 Z2 Z3 Z4 Z5 Z6 Z7 ... <- doesn't belong to any block (nr = 4)
1039//
1040// This traversal order must be the same as in default gemm_pack_rhs defined in
1041// GeneralBlockPanelKernel.h.
1042//
1043// *) nr - number of registers along the 'n' dimension.
1044// See GeneralBlockPanelKernel.h and "Anatomy of High-Performance Matrix
1045// Multiplication" paper.
1046template <typename NewDimension, Index Rows, Index Cols, typename ArgType,
1047 typename Device, typename Scalar, typename Index,
1048 typename nocontract_t, typename contract_t, int packet_size,
1049 bool inner_dim_contiguous, bool inner_dim_reordered, int Alignment,
1050 int nr>
1051struct gemm_pack_rhs<
1052 Scalar, Index,
1053 TensorContractionSubMapper<
1054 Scalar, Index, Rhs,
1055 TensorEvaluator<
1056 const TensorReshapingOp<
1057 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
1058 Device>,
1059 nocontract_t, contract_t, packet_size, inner_dim_contiguous,
1060 inner_dim_reordered, Alignment>,
1061 nr, ColMajor, false, false> {
1062 typedef TensorContractionSubMapper<
1063 Scalar, Index, Rhs,
1064 TensorEvaluator<
1065 const TensorReshapingOp<
1066 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
1067 Device>,
1068 nocontract_t, contract_t, packet_size, inner_dim_contiguous,
1069 inner_dim_reordered, Alignment>
1070 SubMapper;
1071 typedef SubMapper DataMapper;
1072 typedef typename packet_traits<Scalar>::type Packet;
1073
1074 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT((nr == 4), YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE)
1075
1076 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
1077 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void operator()(Scalar* block, const DataMapper& rhs,
1078 Index depth, Index cols, Index stride = 0,
1079 Index offset = 0) const {
1080 eigen_assert(stride == 0);
1081 eigen_assert(offset == 0);
1082
1083 const Index packet_cols4 = (cols / 4) * 4;
1084 const Index peeled_k = (depth / packet_size) * packet_size;
1085 const bool non_standard_patches = rhs.nonStandardPatches();
1086
1087 for (Index j2 = 0; j2 < packet_cols4; j2 += 4) {
1088 const SubMapper dm0 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 0);
1089 const SubMapper dm1 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 1);
1090 const SubMapper dm2 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 2);
1091 const SubMapper dm3 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 3);
1092
1093 Index k = 0;
1094 if ((packet_size % 4) == 0 && !non_standard_patches) {
1095 // FAST PATH:
1096 // Iterate over patch columns and rows, if we know that a single
1097 // packet do not span across multiple rows or columns.
1098 if ((rhs.patchDepth() % packet_size) == 0) {
1099 const Index start_col = rhs.colOffset();
1100 const Index max_col = rhs.maxCol(peeled_k);
1101
1102 for (Index c = start_col; c < max_col; ++c) {
1103 eigen_assert(k <= peeled_k);
1104
1105 const Index start_row = (c == start_col) ? rhs.rowOffset() : 0;
1106 const Index max_row = rhs.maxRow(peeled_k, c);
1107
1108 const bool pad_col0 = dm0.padCol(c);
1109 const bool pad_col1 = dm1.padCol(c);
1110 const bool pad_col2 = dm2.padCol(c);
1111 const bool pad_col3 = dm3.padCol(c);
1112
1113 // Check if we can squeeze reads along the `row` and `depth`
1114 // dimensions (two innermost dimensions).
1115 if (!pad_col0 && !pad_col1 && !pad_col2 && !pad_col3 && //
1116 !dm0.padRow(start_row) && !dm0.padRow(max_row - 1) && //
1117 !dm1.padRow(start_row) && !dm1.padRow(max_row - 1) && //
1118 !dm2.padRow(start_row) && !dm2.padRow(max_row - 1) && //
1119 !dm3.padRow(start_row) && !dm3.padRow(max_row - 1)) {
1120 // Compute how many elements we can squeeze read.
1121 const Index start_depth =
1122 (c == start_col) ? rhs.depthOffset() : 0;
1123
1124 // Upper bound for the number of elements in the depth dimension
1125 // that we can squeeze read.
1126 const Index squeeze_length =
1127 (max_row - start_row) * rhs.patchDepth() - start_depth;
1128
1129 // Do not overshoot beyond the block size.
1130 const Index max_depth =
1131 start_depth + std::min<Index>(peeled_k - k, squeeze_length);
1132 eigen_assert((max_depth - start_depth) % packet_size == 0);
1133
1134 const Index idx0 = dm0.baseIndex(start_row, c);
1135 const Index idx1 = dm1.baseIndex(start_row, c);
1136 const Index idx2 = dm2.baseIndex(start_row, c);
1137 const Index idx3 = dm3.baseIndex(start_row, c);
1138
1139 for (Index d = start_depth; d < max_depth; d += packet_size) {
1140 eigen_assert(k < peeled_k);
1141 PacketBlock<Packet, 4> kernel;
1142 kernel.packet[0] = rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx0);
1143 kernel.packet[1] = rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx1);
1144 kernel.packet[2] = rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx2);
1145 kernel.packet[3] = rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx3);
1146 ptranspose(kernel);
1147 pstoreu(block + 0 * packet_size, kernel.packet[0]);
1148 pstoreu(block + 1 * packet_size, kernel.packet[1]);
1149 pstoreu(block + 2 * packet_size, kernel.packet[2]);
1150 pstoreu(block + 3 * packet_size, kernel.packet[3]);
1151 block += 4 * packet_size;
1152 k += packet_size;
1153 }
1154
1155 // Go to the next column.
1156 continue;
1157 }
1158
1159 // If we can't squeeze reads, process rows one by one.
1160 for (Index r = start_row; r < max_row; ++r) {
1161 eigen_assert(k <= peeled_k);
1162
1163 const bool pad0 = pad_col0 || dm0.padRow(r);
1164 const bool pad1 = pad_col1 || dm1.padRow(r);
1165 const bool pad2 = pad_col2 || dm2.padRow(r);
1166 const bool pad3 = pad_col3 || dm3.padRow(r);
1167
1168 const Index idx0 = dm0.baseIndex(r, c);
1169 const Index idx1 = dm1.baseIndex(r, c);
1170 const Index idx2 = dm2.baseIndex(r, c);
1171 const Index idx3 = dm3.baseIndex(r, c);
1172
1173 const Index start_depth = ((c == start_col) && (r == start_row))
1174 ? rhs.depthOffset()
1175 : 0;
1176 const Index max_depth = rhs.maxDepth(peeled_k - k, start_depth);
1177 eigen_assert((max_depth - start_depth) % packet_size == 0);
1178
1179 for (Index d = start_depth; d < max_depth; d += packet_size) {
1180 eigen_assert(k < peeled_k);
1181 PacketBlock<Packet, 4> kernel;
1182 kernel.packet[0] = pad0 ? pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0))
1183 : rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx0);
1184 kernel.packet[1] = pad1 ? pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0))
1185 : rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx1);
1186 kernel.packet[2] = pad2 ? pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0))
1187 : rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx2);
1188 kernel.packet[3] = pad3 ? pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0))
1189 : rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx3);
1190 ptranspose(kernel);
1191 pstoreu(block + 0 * packet_size, kernel.packet[0]);
1192 pstoreu(block + 1 * packet_size, kernel.packet[1]);
1193 pstoreu(block + 2 * packet_size, kernel.packet[2]);
1194 pstoreu(block + 3 * packet_size, kernel.packet[3]);
1195 block += 4 * packet_size;
1196 k += packet_size;
1197 }
1198 }
1199 }
1200
1201 // The loop above should fill peeled_k elements.
1202 eigen_assert(peeled_k == k);
1203
1204 } else {
1205 for (; k < peeled_k; k += packet_size) {
1206 PacketBlock<Packet, 4> kernel;
1207 kernel.packet[0] = dm0.loadPacketStandard(k);
1208 kernel.packet[1] = dm1.loadPacketStandard(k);
1209 kernel.packet[2] = dm2.loadPacketStandard(k);
1210 kernel.packet[3] = dm3.loadPacketStandard(k);
1211 ptranspose(kernel);
1212 pstoreu(block + 0 * packet_size, kernel.packet[0]);
1213 pstoreu(block + 1 * packet_size, kernel.packet[1]);
1214 pstoreu(block + 2 * packet_size, kernel.packet[2]);
1215 pstoreu(block + 3 * packet_size, kernel.packet[3]);
1216 block += 4 * packet_size;
1217 }
1218 }
1219 }
1220
1221 // Copy the remaining coefficients of the column block after the peeled_k.
1222 if (!rhs.nonStandardPatches()) {
1223 for (; k < depth; k++) {
1224 block[0] = dm0.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1225 block[1] = dm1.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1226 block[2] = dm2.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1227 block[3] = dm3.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1228 block += 4;
1229 }
1230 } else {
1231 for (; k < depth; k++) {
1232 block[0] = dm0(k);
1233 block[1] = dm1(k);
1234 block[2] = dm2(k);
1235 block[3] = dm3(k);
1236 block += 4;
1237 }
1238 }
1239 }
1240
1241 // copy the remaining columns one at a time (nr==1)
1242 for (Index j2 = packet_cols4; j2 < cols; ++j2) {
1243 const SubMapper dm0 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2);
1244 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; k++) {
1245 *block = dm0(k);
1246 block += 1;
1247 }
1248 }
1249 }
1250};
1251
1252// Template specialization for packet_size = 2. We must special-case packet
1253// blocks with nr > packet_size, e.g. PacketBlock<Packet2d, 4>.
1254template <typename NewDimension, Index Rows, Index Cols, typename ArgType,
1255 typename Device, typename Scalar, typename Index,
1256 typename nocontract_t, typename contract_t, bool inner_dim_contiguous,
1257 bool inner_dim_reordered, int Alignment, int nr>
1258struct gemm_pack_rhs<
1259 Scalar, Index,
1260 TensorContractionSubMapper<
1261 Scalar, Index, Rhs,
1262 TensorEvaluator<
1263 const TensorReshapingOp<
1264 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
1265 Device>,
1266 nocontract_t, contract_t, 2, inner_dim_contiguous, inner_dim_reordered,
1267 Alignment>,
1268 nr, ColMajor, false, false> {
1269 typedef TensorContractionSubMapper<
1270 Scalar, Index, Rhs,
1271 TensorEvaluator<
1272 const TensorReshapingOp<
1273 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
1274 Device>,
1275 nocontract_t, contract_t, 2, inner_dim_contiguous, inner_dim_reordered,
1276 Alignment>
1277 SubMapper;
1278 typedef SubMapper DataMapper;
1279 typedef typename packet_traits<Scalar>::type Packet;
1280
1281 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT((nr == 4), YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE)
1282
1283 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
1284 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void operator()(Scalar* block, const DataMapper& rhs,
1285 Index depth, Index cols, Index stride = 0,
1286 Index offset = 0) const {
1287 eigen_assert(stride == 0);
1288 eigen_assert(offset == 0);
1289
1290 const int packet_size = 2;
1291 const Index packet_cols4 = (cols / 4) * 4;
1292 const Index peeled_k = (depth / packet_size) * packet_size;
1293 const bool non_standard_patches = rhs.nonStandardPatches();
1294
1295 for (Index j2 = 0; j2 < packet_cols4; j2 += 4) {
1296 const SubMapper dm0 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 0);
1297 const SubMapper dm1 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 1);
1298 const SubMapper dm2 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 2);
1299 const SubMapper dm3 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 3);
1300
1301 Index k = 0;
1302 if (!non_standard_patches) {
1303 // FAST PATH:
1304 // Iterate over patch columns and rows if we know that a single
1305 // packet do not span across multiple rows or columns.
1306 if ((rhs.patchDepth() % packet_size) == 0) {
1307 const Index start_col = rhs.colOffset();
1308 const Index max_col = rhs.maxCol(peeled_k);
1309
1310 for (Index c = start_col; c < max_col; ++c) {
1311 eigen_assert(k <= peeled_k);
1312
1313 const Index start_row = (c == start_col) ? rhs.rowOffset() : 0;
1314 const Index max_row = rhs.maxRow(peeled_k, c);
1315
1316 const bool pad_col0 = dm0.padCol(c);
1317 const bool pad_col1 = dm1.padCol(c);
1318 const bool pad_col2 = dm2.padCol(c);
1319 const bool pad_col3 = dm3.padCol(c);
1320
1321 // We can squeeze reads along the `row` and `depth` dimensions if
1322 // the row stride is `1`, which means that `row` and `depth`
1323 // dimensions are contiguous (two innermost dimensions).
1324 if (rhs.rowStride() == 1 && //
1325 !pad_col0 && !pad_col1 && !pad_col2 && !pad_col3 && //
1326 !dm0.padRow(start_row) && !dm0.padRow(max_row - 1) && //
1327 !dm1.padRow(start_row) && !dm1.padRow(max_row - 1) && //
1328 !dm2.padRow(start_row) && !dm2.padRow(max_row - 1) && //
1329 !dm3.padRow(start_row) && !dm3.padRow(max_row - 1)) {
1330 // Compute how many elements we can squeeze read.
1331 const Index start_depth =
1332 (c == start_col) ? rhs.depthOffset() : 0;
1333
1334 // Upper bound for the number of elements in the depth dimension
1335 // that we can squeeze read.
1336 const Index squeeze_length =
1337 (max_row - start_row) * rhs.patchDepth() - start_depth;
1338
1339 // Do not overshoot beyond the block size.
1340 const Index max_depth =
1341 start_depth + std::min<Index>(peeled_k - k, squeeze_length);
1342 eigen_assert((max_depth - start_depth) % packet_size == 0);
1343
1344 const Index idx0 = dm0.baseIndex(start_row, c);
1345 const Index idx1 = dm1.baseIndex(start_row, c);
1346 const Index idx2 = dm2.baseIndex(start_row, c);
1347 const Index idx3 = dm3.baseIndex(start_row, c);
1348
1349 for (Index d = start_depth; d < max_depth; d += packet_size) {
1350 PacketBlock<Packet, 2> kernel0;
1351 PacketBlock<Packet, 2> kernel1;
1352 kernel0.packet[0] = rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx0);
1353 kernel0.packet[1] = rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx1);
1354 kernel1.packet[0] = rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx2);
1355 kernel1.packet[1] = rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx3);
1356 ptranspose(kernel0);
1357 ptranspose(kernel1);
1358 pstoreu(block + 0 * packet_size, kernel0.packet[0]);
1359 pstoreu(block + 1 * packet_size, kernel1.packet[0]);
1360 pstoreu(block + 2 * packet_size, kernel0.packet[1]);
1361 pstoreu(block + 3 * packet_size, kernel1.packet[1]);
1362 block += 4 * packet_size;
1363 k += packet_size;
1364 }
1365
1366 // Go to the next column.
1367 continue;
1368 }
1369
1370 // If we can't squeeze reads, process rows one by one.
1371 for (Index r = start_row; r < max_row; ++r) {
1372 eigen_assert(k <= peeled_k);
1373
1374 const bool pad0 = pad_col0 || dm0.padRow(r);
1375 const bool pad1 = pad_col1 || dm1.padRow(r);
1376 const bool pad2 = pad_col2 || dm2.padRow(r);
1377 const bool pad3 = pad_col3 || dm3.padRow(r);
1378
1379 const Index idx0 = dm0.baseIndex(r, c);
1380 const Index idx1 = dm1.baseIndex(r, c);
1381 const Index idx2 = dm2.baseIndex(r, c);
1382 const Index idx3 = dm3.baseIndex(r, c);
1383
1384 const Index start_depth = ((c == start_col) && (r == start_row))
1385 ? rhs.depthOffset()
1386 : 0;
1387 const Index max_depth = rhs.maxDepth(peeled_k - k, start_depth);
1388 eigen_assert((max_depth - start_depth) % packet_size == 0);
1389
1390 for (Index d = start_depth; d < max_depth; d += packet_size) {
1391 eigen_assert(k < peeled_k);
1392 PacketBlock<Packet, 2> kernel0;
1393 PacketBlock<Packet, 2> kernel1;
1394 kernel0.packet[0] = pad0 ? pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0))
1395 : rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx0);
1396 kernel0.packet[1] = pad1 ? pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0))
1397 : rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx1);
1398 kernel1.packet[0] = pad2 ? pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0))
1399 : rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx2);
1400 kernel1.packet[1] = pad3 ? pset1<Packet>(Scalar(0))
1401 : rhs.packetNoPadding(d, idx3);
1402 ptranspose(kernel0);
1403 ptranspose(kernel1);
1404 pstoreu(block + 0 * packet_size, kernel0.packet[0]);
1405 pstoreu(block + 1 * packet_size, kernel1.packet[0]);
1406 pstoreu(block + 2 * packet_size, kernel0.packet[1]);
1407 pstoreu(block + 3 * packet_size, kernel1.packet[1]);
1408 block += 4 * packet_size;
1409 k += packet_size;
1410 }
1411 }
1412 }
1413
1414 // The loop above should fill peeled_k elements.
1415 eigen_assert(peeled_k == k);
1416
1417 } else {
1418 // Packet can span multiple rows or columns, so we have to go
1419 // though the slower "standard" path.
1420 for (; k < peeled_k; k += packet_size) {
1421 PacketBlock<Packet, 2> kernel0;
1422 PacketBlock<Packet, 2> kernel1;
1423 kernel0.packet[0] = dm0.loadPacketStandard(k);
1424 kernel0.packet[1] = dm1.loadPacketStandard(k);
1425 kernel1.packet[0] = dm2.loadPacketStandard(k);
1426 kernel1.packet[1] = dm3.loadPacketStandard(k);
1427 ptranspose(kernel0);
1428 ptranspose(kernel1);
1429 pstoreu(block + 0 * packet_size, kernel0.packet[0]);
1430 pstoreu(block + 1 * packet_size, kernel1.packet[0]);
1431 pstoreu(block + 2 * packet_size, kernel0.packet[1]);
1432 pstoreu(block + 3 * packet_size, kernel1.packet[1]);
1433 block += 4 * packet_size;
1434 }
1435 }
1436 }
1437
1438 // Copy the remaining coefficients of the column block after the peeled_k.
1439 if (!non_standard_patches) {
1440 for (; k < depth; k++) {
1441 block[0] = dm0.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1442 block[1] = dm1.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1443 block[2] = dm2.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1444 block[3] = dm3.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1445 block += 4;
1446 }
1447 } else {
1448 for (; k < depth; k++) {
1449 block[0] = dm0(k);
1450 block[1] = dm1(k);
1451 block[2] = dm2(k);
1452 block[3] = dm3(k);
1453 block += 4;
1454 }
1455 }
1456 }
1457
1458 // Copy the remaining columns one at a time (nr==1).
1459 for (Index j2 = packet_cols4; j2 < cols; ++j2) {
1460 const SubMapper dm0 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2);
1461 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; k++) {
1462 *block = dm0(k);
1463 block += 1;
1464 }
1465 }
1466 }
1467};

1469// Special case for non-vectorized types such as float16.
1470template <typename NewDimension, Index Rows, Index Cols, typename ArgType,
1471 typename Device, typename Scalar, typename Index,
1472 typename nocontract_t, typename contract_t, bool inner_dim_contiguous,
1473 bool inner_dim_reordered, int Alignment, int nr>
1474struct gemm_pack_rhs<
1475 Scalar, Index,
1476 TensorContractionSubMapper<
1477 Scalar, Index, Rhs,
1478 TensorEvaluator<
1479 const TensorReshapingOp<
1480 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
1481 Device>,
1482 nocontract_t, contract_t, 1, inner_dim_contiguous, inner_dim_reordered,
1483 Alignment>,
1484 nr, ColMajor, false, false> {
1485 typedef TensorContractionSubMapper<
1486 Scalar, Index, Rhs,
1487 TensorEvaluator<
1488 const TensorReshapingOp<
1489 NewDimension, const TensorImagePatchOp<Rows, Cols, ArgType> >,
1490 Device>,
1491 nocontract_t, contract_t, 1, inner_dim_contiguous, inner_dim_reordered,
1492 Alignment>
1493 SubMapper;
1494 typedef SubMapper DataMapper;
1495
1496 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT((nr == 4), YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE)
1497
1498 EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
1499 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void operator()(Scalar* block, const DataMapper& rhs,
1500 Index depth, Index cols, Index stride = 0,
1501 Index offset = 0) const {
1502 eigen_assert(stride == 0);
1503 eigen_assert(offset == 0);
1504
1505 const Index packet_cols4 = (cols / 4) * 4;
1506
1507 for (Index j2 = 0; j2 < packet_cols4; j2 += 4) {
1508 const SubMapper dm0 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 0);
1509 const SubMapper dm1 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 1);
1510 const SubMapper dm2 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 2);
1511 const SubMapper dm3 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2 + 3);
1512
1513 if (!rhs.nonStandardPatches()) {
1514 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; k++) {
1515 block[0] = dm0.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1516 block[1] = dm1.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1517 block[2] = dm2.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1518 block[3] = dm3.loadCoeffStandard(k);
1519 block += 4;
1520 }
1521 } else {
1522 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; k++) {
1523 block[0] = dm0(k);
1524 block[1] = dm1(k);
1525 block[2] = dm2(k);
1526 block[3] = dm3(k);
1527 block += 4;
1528 }
1529 }
1530 }
1531
1532 // Copy the remaining columns one at a time (nr==1).
1533 for (Index j2 = packet_cols4; j2 < cols; ++j2) {
1534 const SubMapper dm0 = rhs.getLinearMapper(0, j2);
1535 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; k++) {
1536 *block = dm0(k);
1537 block += 1;
1538 }
1539 }
1540 }
1541};
1542#endif

1545/** SpatialConvolution
1546 * \ingroup CXX11_NeuralNetworks_Module
1547 *
1548 * \brief Applies a 2D convolution over a multichannel input image.
1549 *
1550 * The input parameter is expected to be a tensor with a rank of 3 or more
1551 * (channels, height, width, and optionally others)
1552 * The kernel parameter is expected to be a 4D tensor (filters, channels,
1553 * kernel_height, kernel_width)
1554 * The input and the kernel must both be in col-major layout. The result will
1555 * also be in col-major layout.
1556 *
1557 * If col_in_stride, row_in_stride > 1, then applies convolution with holes
1558 * (aka atrous convolution), sampling every col_in_stride, row_in_stride input
1559 * pixels.
1560 *
1561 * If padding_top, padding_bottom, padding_left, or padding_right is specified,
1562 * then those paddings will be used to pad the input, and padding_type must be
1563 * PADDING_VALID.
1564 *
1565 * The result can be assigned to a tensor of rank equal to the rank of the
1566 * input. The dimensions of the result will be filters, height, width (and
1567 * others if applicable).
1568 *
1569 * It is possible to swap the order of the width and height dimensions provided
1570 * that the same order is used in the input, the kernel, and the output.
1571 *
1572 * It is also possible to add an output kernel to the contraction, output
1573 * kernel is called by Eigen when it "finalizes" the block of an output tensor.
1574 *
1575 */
1576template <typename Input, typename Kernel,
1577 typename OutputKernel = const NoOpOutputKernel>
1578EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC
1579 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE static const typename internal::conditional<
1580 internal::traits<Input>::Layout == ColMajor,
1581 TensorReshapingOp<
1582 const DSizes<typename internal::traits<Input>::Index,
1583 internal::traits<Input>::NumDimensions>,
1584 const TensorContractionOp<
1585 const array<IndexPair<typename internal::traits<Input>::Index>,
1586 1>,
1587 const TensorReshapingOp<
1588 const DSizes<typename internal::traits<Input>::Index, 2>,
1589 const Kernel>,
1590 const TensorReshapingOp<
1591 const DSizes<typename internal::traits<Input>::Index, 2>,
1592 const TensorImagePatchOp<Dynamic, Dynamic, const Input> >,
1593 const OutputKernel> >,
1594 TensorReshapingOp<
1595 const DSizes<typename internal::traits<Input>::Index,
1596 internal::traits<Input>::NumDimensions>,
1597 const TensorContractionOp<
1598 const array<IndexPair<typename internal::traits<Input>::Index>,
1599 1>,
1600 const TensorReshapingOp<
1601 const DSizes<typename internal::traits<Input>::Index, 2>,
1602 const TensorImagePatchOp<Dynamic, Dynamic, const Input> >,
1603 const TensorReshapingOp<
1604 const DSizes<typename internal::traits<Input>::Index, 2>,
1605 const Kernel>,
1606 const OutputKernel> > >::type
1607 SpatialConvolution(const Input& input, const Kernel& kernel,
1608 const Index row_stride = 1, const Index col_stride = 1,
1609 const PaddingType padding_type = PADDING_SAME,
1610 const Index row_in_stride = 1,
1611 const Index col_in_stride = 1,
1612 const OutputKernel& output_kernel = OutputKernel(),
1613 Index padding_top = 0, Index padding_bottom = 0,
1614 Index padding_left = 0, Index padding_right = 0) {
1615 typedef typename internal::traits<Input>::Index TensorIndex;
1616 TensorRef<Tensor<typename internal::traits<Input>::Scalar,
1617 internal::traits<Input>::NumDimensions,
1618 internal::traits<Input>::Layout, TensorIndex> >
1619 in(input);
1620 TensorRef<Tensor<typename internal::traits<Kernel>::Scalar,
1621 internal::traits<Kernel>::NumDimensions,
1622 internal::traits<Kernel>::Layout, TensorIndex> >
1623 kern(kernel);
1624
1625 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT(
1626 internal::traits<Input>::Layout == internal::traits<Kernel>::Layout,
1627 YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE)
1628 const bool isColMajor = (internal::traits<Input>::Layout == ColMajor);
1629
1630 const int NumDims = internal::traits<Input>::NumDimensions;
1631
1632 // Number of filters to apply. This is the same as the output depth of the
1633 // result
1634 const TensorIndex kernelFilters =
1635 isColMajor ? kern.dimensions()[0] : kern.dimensions()[3];
1636 // Number of channels. This is the same as the input depth.
1637 const TensorIndex kernelChannels =
1638 isColMajor ? kern.dimensions()[1] : kern.dimensions()[2];
1639 const TensorIndex kernelRows =
1640 isColMajor ? kern.dimensions()[2] : kern.dimensions()[1];
1641 const TensorIndex kernelCols =
1642 isColMajor ? kern.dimensions()[3] : kern.dimensions()[0];
1643
1644 const Index kernelRowsEff =
1645 kernelRows + (kernelRows - 1) * (row_in_stride - 1);
1646 const Index kernelColsEff =
1647 kernelCols + (kernelCols - 1) * (col_in_stride - 1);
1648
1649 array<IndexPair<TensorIndex>, 1> contract_dims;
1650 contract_dims[0] = IndexPair<TensorIndex>(1, 0);
1651
1652 const TensorIndex InputRows =
1653 isColMajor ? in.dimension(1) : in.dimension(NumDims - 2);
1654 const TensorIndex InputCols =
1655 isColMajor ? in.dimension(2) : in.dimension(NumDims - 3);
1656 const bool padding_explicit =
1657 (padding_top || padding_bottom || padding_left || padding_right);
1658
1659 TensorIndex out_height;
1660 TensorIndex out_width;
1661 switch (padding_type) {
1662 case PADDING_VALID: {
1663 const TensorIndex InputRowsEff = InputRows + padding_top + padding_bottom;
1664 const TensorIndex InputColsEff = InputCols + padding_left + padding_right;
1665 out_height = divup(InputRowsEff - kernelRowsEff + 1, row_stride);
1666 out_width = divup(InputColsEff - kernelColsEff + 1, col_stride);
1667 break;
1668 }
1669 case PADDING_SAME: {
1670 eigen_assert(!padding_explicit);
1671 out_height = divup(InputRows, row_stride);
1672 out_width = divup(InputCols, col_stride);
1673 break;
1674 }
1675 default: {
1676 // Initialize unused variables to avoid a compiler warning
1677 out_height = 0;
1678 out_width = 0;
1679 eigen_assert(false && "unexpected padding");
1680 }
1681 }
1682
1683 // Molds the output of the patch extraction code into a 2d tensor:
1684 // - the first dimension (dims[0]): the patch values to be multiplied with the
1685 // kernels
1686 // - the second dimension (dims[1]): everything else
1687 DSizes<TensorIndex, 2> pre_contract_dims;
1688 if (isColMajor) {
1689 pre_contract_dims[0] = kernelChannels * kernelRows * kernelCols;
1690 pre_contract_dims[1] = out_height * out_width;
1691 for (int i = 3; i < NumDims; ++i) {
1692 pre_contract_dims[1] *= in.dimension(i);
1693 }
1694 } else {
1695 pre_contract_dims[1] = kernelChannels * kernelRows * kernelCols;
1696 pre_contract_dims[0] = out_height * out_width;
1697 for (int i = 0; i < NumDims - 3; ++i) {
1698 pre_contract_dims[0] *= in.dimension(i);
1699 }
1700 }
1701
1702 // Molds the output of the contraction into the shape expected by the used
1703 // (assuming this is ColMajor):
1704 // - 1st dim: kernel filters
1705 // - 2nd dim: output height
1706 // - 3rd dim: output width
1707 // - 4th dim and beyond: everything else including batch size
1708 DSizes<TensorIndex, NumDims> post_contract_dims;
1709 if (isColMajor) {
1710 post_contract_dims[0] = kernelFilters;
1711 post_contract_dims[1] = out_height;
1712 post_contract_dims[2] = out_width;
1713 for (int i = 3; i < NumDims; ++i) {
1714 post_contract_dims[i] = in.dimension(i);
1715 }
1716 } else {
1717 post_contract_dims[NumDims - 1] = kernelFilters;
1718 post_contract_dims[NumDims - 2] = out_height;
1719 post_contract_dims[NumDims - 3] = out_width;
1720 for (int i = 0; i < NumDims - 3; ++i) {
1721 post_contract_dims[i] = in.dimension(i);
1722 }
1723 }
1724
1725 DSizes<TensorIndex, 2> kernel_dims;
1726 if (isColMajor) {
1727 kernel_dims[0] = kernelFilters;
1728 kernel_dims[1] = kernelChannels * kernelRows * kernelCols;
1729 } else {
1730 kernel_dims[0] = kernelChannels * kernelRows * kernelCols;
1731 kernel_dims[1] = kernelFilters;
1732 }
1733 if (padding_explicit) {
1734 return choose(
1735 Cond<internal::traits<Input>::Layout == ColMajor>(),
1736 kernel.reshape(kernel_dims)
1737 .contract(input
1738 .extract_image_patches(
1739 kernelRows, kernelCols, row_stride, col_stride,
1740 row_in_stride, col_in_stride,
1741 /*row_inflate_stride=*/1,
1742 /*col_inflate_stride=*/1, padding_top,
1743 padding_bottom, padding_left, padding_right,
1744 /*padding_value=*/0)
1745 .reshape(pre_contract_dims),
1746 contract_dims, output_kernel)
1747 .reshape(post_contract_dims),
1748 input
1749 .extract_image_patches(kernelRows, kernelCols, row_stride,
1750 col_stride, row_in_stride, col_in_stride,
1751 /*row_inflate_stride=*/1,
1752 /*col_inflate_stride=*/1, padding_top,
1753 padding_bottom, padding_left, padding_right,
1754 /*padding_value=*/0)
1755 .reshape(pre_contract_dims)
1756 .contract(kernel.reshape(kernel_dims), contract_dims, output_kernel)
1757 .reshape(post_contract_dims));
1758 } else {
1759 return choose(
1760 Cond<internal::traits<Input>::Layout == ColMajor>(),
1761 kernel.reshape(kernel_dims)
1762 .contract(input
1763 .extract_image_patches(
1764 kernelRows, kernelCols, row_stride, col_stride,
1765 row_in_stride, col_in_stride, padding_type)
1766 .reshape(pre_contract_dims),
1767 contract_dims, output_kernel)
1768 .reshape(post_contract_dims),
1769 input
1770 .extract_image_patches(kernelRows, kernelCols, row_stride,
1771 col_stride, row_in_stride, col_in_stride,
1772 padding_type)
1773 .reshape(pre_contract_dims)
1774 .contract(kernel.reshape(kernel_dims), contract_dims, output_kernel)
1775 .reshape(post_contract_dims));
1776 }
1777}
1778
1779} // end namespace Eigen
